a:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI1MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMzY0IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNTAwIDM2NCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgc3R5bGU9ImZpbGw6I2NmZDRkYjtmaWxsLW9wYWNpdHk6IDAuMTsiLz48L3N2Zz4=)']

Section: Nova Cultura

Tags: ['Dorival Caymmi']

Type: article

<!--METADATA-->

![](Images/A Nova Democracia/2023-02-26T05-00-00-03-00/Dorival-junto-a-pescadores.jpg)Dorival Caymmi next to fishermen. Photo: Reproduction

- Did you achieve your goal with your work?

**- I hit. I arrive, my people know me. My glory is this. **(Dorival Caymmi interview at the age of 90 to “The Municipality Online”)Dorival Caymmi is one of the giants of our popular culture, representative of what we best produce historically: singer, composer, researcherusical, instrumentalist, poet, artist artist(having made the cover of some of their own albums)and even actor.

His music production moves among the famous Praieiras songs, sambas-song, waltzes, etc. A master of synthesis, Dorival Caymmi made up the simple, longing, constantly reworking his songs, polishing them for several decades: in 60 years of career, he composed a maximum of 100 songs. In their own lyrics, there are images of the country's life of the country's massbeators, more specifically, of fishermen and other sea workers, their faith, customs, particularities and the way they have entered the constant struggle for production, expressed with great passion esensitivity.

** “Let's call the wind **

** Wind that gives the candle **

** Candle that takes the boat **

** boat that takes us **

** People who take the fish **

** Fish that gives money, Curimã ” - The Wind **

His realistic posture of artistic expression took his great friend, the Titanic Titanicist Jorge Amado, to say once: “If he had the gift of singing ecompor, he would sing Caymmi's songs. If he stopped singing to write Romances, he would certainly write mine. "

In his faithful portrayal of Bahia's customs and traditions, he told the life of typical characters. This is also expressed in stylistic their resquire, such as rescuing the corners(gifts in compositions such as “fishing” and “fisherman suite”), and even in the hit that employs on the guitar, learned from the rafts. As I said in its ** songbook of Bahia **, “the blacks and mulattoes that have their lives tied sea have been my most permanent inspiration. I don't know of more powerful drama than that of women who expect the back, always uncertain, the husbands leave every morning to the sea in the bulge of the light savers or the mosquitoe rafts. ”** "This is a story of fishermen. It is a story of sea men. For the fisherman, the sea is a seduction. For the fisherman, the sea is also the fur struggle. Each one carries a story in the chest. A story From your love Naterra that can be as great as your love for the sea. But the fisherman is called by the sun, he goes. He goes to the sea, to the fish. And every morning, he sing a corner of faith where he praises his Raft, your sea, your work. Where also praises an eternal hope that a good fish can transit, God willing. ”**

He highlights first of all the lead role of the struggle for production in the life of the dopecator, which despite the risk inherent in the craft and knowing that he may not return home at the end of the day, praises his work instrument(the raft, acanoa, the sloop), and its work environment that is the sea. This expectation is in the form of the following work song, whose rhythm of the lows in the instruments and words pulling the nets and the beating of the oars(Rhythm also present in your “_Pecaria(Canoe)”, _De 1954).

**Minha jangada vai sair pro mar**

**Vou trabalhar, meu bem querer**

**Se Deus quiser quando eu voltar do mar**

**Um peixe bom eu vou trazer**

**Meus companheiros também vão voltar**

**E a Deus do céu vamos agradecer**

**(Fisherman History, Part I - Song of the match)**

In addition to the faith and hope of those who go, the opera also illustrates the apprehension and omemor of those who stay. The wives, brides, children, friends of the workers who expense the return of the dear person, and who can do nothing but to take their own faith, and wait patiently.

In this opera, as in many other compositions(Some of them referenced in the opera), as "it is sweet to die in the sea", "the raft has come back" and "The Sea", the fishermen find their last end in the waters of "Iemanjá", and never return to their community, to their homes, wives and children. In “_ _History of fishermen”, _Why, something different happens: the fisherman, dady dead that storm night, returns the next morning. The part drove the work corner of Part I. It starts, along with the song, a work novodia. The fisherman's near-death experience is an event, which will happen again.This Caymmi was able to apprehend by his investigation of popular culture intimate erelation with the masses, comprising real trends and needs his life: the struggle for production, the understandings of the world, the forms describing, the cultural singularities and their creative character. Of this form and only in this way, he could leave us the rich eternal legacy of his artistic production; And besides, as is the reason for his pride, served by the people as a genuine representative of his.

See here more images of Dorival Caymmi:

![](Images/A Nova Democracia/2023-02-26T05-00-00-03-00/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI3ODAiIGhlaWdodD0iNDkwIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNzgwIDQ5MCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgc3R5bGU9ImZpbGw6I2NmZDRkYjtmaWxsLW9wYWNpdHk6IDAuMTsiLz48L3N2Zz4=)Dorival Caymmi. Photo: Reproduction![](Images/A Nova Democracia/2023-02-26T05-00-00-03-00/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI5NjAiIGhlaWdodD0iNjQwIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgOTYwIDY0MCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgc3R5bGU9ImZpbGw6I2NmZDRkYjtmaWxsLW9wYWNpdHk6IDAuMTsiLz48L3N2Zz4=)Dorivale Jorge Amado. Photo: Reproduction![](Images/A Nova Democracia/2023-02-26T05-00-00-03-00/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI3NzIiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAyNCIgdmlld0JveD0iMCAwIDc3MiAxMDI0Ij48cmVjdCB3aWR0aD0iMTAwJSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxMDAlIiBzdHlsZT0iZmlsbDojY2ZkNGRiO2ZpbGwtb3BhY2l0eTogMC4xOyIvPjwvc3ZnPg==)Dorivaltoca the drum with communities. Photo: Reproduction![](Images/A Nova Democracia/2023-02-26T05-00-00-03-00/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI1MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMzY0IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNTAwIDM2NCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgc3R5bGU9ImZpbGw6I2NmZDRkYjtmaWxsLW9wYWNpdHk6IDAuMTsiLz48L3N2Zz4=)Dorivaljunct to fishermen. Photo: Reproduction

