The last witness of the audience was ** Facundo Luis Guerra **, son of Manuelguerra and Teresita Castrillejo. He reported how his mother left him in care for companions to be able to claim for his father's life. , militating in Mothers of Plaza de Mayo and he in the decaded of the 90s with the formation of children, as part of a generation to whom Robaronsus parents but who were finding brothers and grandmothers. In 2006, his mother requested in justice the progress of the investigation, and also when the plaque that links his father with Atlético was found, facts that add to the testimonies of those who saw him there.He also expressed the need to investigate those who were in charge of the 6 Court 5, such as Dr. de Cejas, where the first hababeas Corpus was presented at the time of the disappearance since there they were considered here you attended by claiming for the whereabouts of loved ones Disappeared that they should not get involved if they wanted to find them. That court "looked for the investigation" for the disappearance of her father, he said. He also claimed the link between the Federal Police, the Prefecture and the Army, not only for the kidnappings that were made often but also with respect to the destiny of the detainees and disappeared. He also pointed out that it is impossible that there are no files when an act is worked when a furniture moves, "we demand that the archives be opened," he said.

